snippet.textDisplay: I’m no wordsmith so I’ll keep it simple (but not short). his image and mindset bothered me at one point, I don’t value pc concepts but I thought one should hold themselves to the standard of showing some self respect, But really his points are entirely reproachful of a system he dislikes while being fluent and articulating his points more than just swearing and telling em to shut up. His music is his own, labeling it rap or hip hop is a waste of time, rather just value if you like it and don’t get caught up on pc terms or his image. He looks different but his words mark him as talented and driven, with strong opinions about the world. Guessing no one’s going to see this but really I just think he defines how even if you don’t agree with someone or even a system, you can still hold yourself to your own standards and speak out against it, without devolving into brutality or ignorance. I’ve come to love his music and value hearing what he thinks throughout his songs, can’t wait to hear more
